fields.name: AddonFeatures
fields.description: List of add-on features to enable on the cluster.

fields.name: AdminPassword
fields.description: VM admin user password.

fields.name: AdminUserName
fields.description: VM admin user name.

fields.name: AllowRdpAccess
fields.description: Setting this to true enables RDP access to the VM. The default NSG rule opens RDP port to Internet which can be overridden with custom Network Security Rules. The default value for this setting is false.

fields.name: ApplicationTypeVersionsCleanupPolicy
fields.description: The policy used to clean up unused versions.

fields.name: AuxiliarySubnets
fields.description: Auxiliary subnets for the cluster.

fields.name: AzureActiveDirectory
fields.description: The AAD authentication settings of the cluster.

fields.name: ClientConnectionPort
fields.description: The port used for client connections to the cluster.

fields.name: Clients
fields.description: Client certificates that are allowed to manage the cluster.

fields.name: ClusterCertificateThumbprints
fields.description: List of thumbprints of the cluster certificates.

fields.name: ClusterCodeVersion
fields.description: The Service Fabric runtime version of the cluster. This property is required when **clusterUpgradeMode** is set to 'Manual'. To get list of available Service Fabric versions for new clusters use [ClusterVersion API](./ClusterVersion.md). To get the list of available version for existing clusters use **availableClusterVersions**.

fields.name: ClusterId
fields.description: A service generated unique identifier for the cluster resource.

fields.name: ClusterState
fields.description: The current state of the cluster.

fields.name: ClusterUpgradeCadence
fields.description: Indicates when new cluster runtime version upgrades will be applied after they are released. By default is Wave0. Only applies when **clusterUpgradeMode** is set to 'Automatic'.

fields.name: DnsName
fields.description: The cluster dns name.

fields.name: EnableAutoOSUpgrade
fields.description: Setting this to true enables automatic OS upgrade for the node types that are created using any platform OS image with version 'latest'. The default value for this setting is false.

fields.name: EnableIPv6
fields.description: Setting this to true creates IPv6 address space for the default VNet used by the cluster. This setting cannot be changed once the cluster is created. The default value for this setting is false.

fields.name: EnableServicePublicIP
fields.description: Setting this to true will link the IPv4 address as the ServicePublicIP of the IPv6 address. It can only be set to True if IPv6 is enabled on the cluster.

fields.name: FabricSettings
fields.description: The list of custom fabric settings to configure the cluster.

fields.name: Fqdn
fields.description: The fully qualified domain name associated with the public load balancer of the cluster.

fields.name: HTTPGatewayConnectionPort
fields.description: The port used for HTTP connections to the cluster.

fields.name: IPTags
fields.description: The list of IP tags associated with the default public IP address of the cluster.

fields.name: IPv4Address
fields.description: The IPv4 address associated with the public load balancer of the cluster.

fields.name: IPv6Address
fields.description: IPv6 address for the cluster if IPv6 is enabled.

fields.name: LoadBalancingRules
fields.description: Load balancing rules that are applied to the public load balancer of the cluster.

fields.name: NetworkSecurityRules
fields.description: Custom Network Security Rules that are applied to the Virtual Network of the cluster.

fields.name: ProvisioningState
fields.description: The provisioning state of the managed cluster resource.

fields.name: ServiceEndpoints
fields.description: Service endpoints for subnets in the cluster.

fields.name: SubnetId
fields.description: If specified, the node types for the cluster are created in this subnet instead of the default VNet. The **networkSecurityRules** specified for the cluster are also applied to this subnet. This setting cannot be changed once the cluster is created.

fields.name: ZonalResiliency
fields.description: Indicates if the cluster has zone resiliency.
